<h1>Binary releases of HPCToolkit GUI interfaces</h1>

<h2>Requirements</h2>
<ul>
	<li>On all platforms: Java 11 (Java 15 does not work for the Linux and Windows version) </li>
	<li>On Linux: GTK 3.20 or newer</li>
</ul>
<h3> Installing Java 11</h3>
The instructions to install Java:
<ol>
	<li>Download Java JDK
		<ul>
			<li>Recommended: <code>spack install openjdk</code></li>
			<li>Or download from <a href="https://www.oracle.com/java/technologies/javase-downloads.html">Oracle</a> or <a href="https://adoptopenjdk.net">AdoptOpenJDK</a> </li>
		</ul>
	</li>
	<li>Set <b><code>JAVA_HOME</code></b> environment variable to the installed directory</li>
	<li> For Mac OS users: in case some Java versions were already installed
		<ul>
			<li>Leave all JDKs at their default location, under <code>/Library/Java/JavaVirtualMachines</code>. The system will pick the highest version by default. </li>
			<li>To exclude a JDK from being picked by default, rename its <code>Contents/Info.plist</code> to: <code>Info.plist.disabled</code>. <br/>
				That JDK can still be used when <code>$JAVA_HOME</code> points to it, or explicitly referenced in a script or configuration. It will simply be ignored by system's java command.</li>
		</ul>
	</li>
</ol>


